headline: This 5.3%-Yielding Dividend Stock Has Maintained Its Payment for 25 Quarters in a Row. Can That Streak Continue in 2025?
summary: Dividends can be a great way to book a return on your investment portfolio no matter what stock prices are doing.  Packaged food giant Kraft Heinz (NASDAQ: KHC) yields about 5.3%, which is more than investors can get from most high-yield savings accounts or a 10-year Treasury bond.  Here's a look at whether Kraft can support its payout and if this high-yield dividend stock is worth buying now.

headline: All the Stocks Warren Buffett Bought in the Last 2 Recessions: Are They Smart Picks Now?
summary: The U.S. economy is "perilously close to slipping into recession" because of President Donald Trump's tariffs, according to JPMorgan Chase chief economist Michael Feroli.  Warren Buffett famously said he likes to "be fearful when others are greedy and greedy when others are fearful."  What kinds of stocks might Buffett buy if a recession is on the way?
